<p><strong>What is the importance of practicing scales and arpeggios?</strong></p>
<p>Practicing scales and arpeggios is essential for any musician. They provide a foundation for technical development and improve finger coordination, dexterity, and accuracy. Scales also help develop a strong understanding of music theory and enhance overall musicality.</p>
<p><strong>Why are scales and arpeggios included in the "The Aristocats" sheet music PDF?</strong></p>
<p>The "The Aristocats" sheet music PDF includes scales and arpeggios to assist musicians in mastering the technical aspects of the piece. These exercises serve as warm-ups and help players develop the necessary skills to perform the music accurately and expressively.</p>
