<p><strong>How often should musicians practice scales and arpeggios?</strong></p>
<p>The frequency of practice varies depending on the musician's skill level and goals. A general recommendation is to spend at least 15-30 minutes per day practicing scales and arpeggios. Consistent practice over time will yield significant improvements in technical ability.</p>
